# Azure-DevOpsUserStoryManager Local Rules

## Overview

This folder contains the Azure DevOps work item management script and supporting files.

**Main Script:** `Azure-DevOpsUserStoryManager.ps1`

---

## Available Actions

| Action | Purpose | Required Parameters |
|--------|---------|-------------------|
| `Get` | Retrieve work item details | `-WorkItemId` |
| `Update` | Modify work item description | `-WorkItemId`, `-Description` |
| `Comment` | Add discussion comment | `-WorkItemId`, `-Comment` |
| `Attach` | Upload file attachment | `-WorkItemId`, `-FilePath` |
| `Link` | Add repository link or hyperlink | `-WorkItemId`, `-Url`, `-Title` |
| `Status` | Change work item state | `-WorkItemId`, `-State` |
| `Subtask` | Create child task | `-WorkItemId`, `-Title`, `-Description` |
| `AddTags` | Add tags to work item | `-WorkItemId`, `-Tags` (semicolon-separated) |

---

## Language Standards

- **Titles and descriptions for new work items**: Use **Norwegian** (Bokmål)
- **Comments**: Can be English or Norwegian, prefer Norwegian for consistency
- **Tags**: Use English for technical tags (e.g., `BugFix`, `Tested`, `ReadyForReview`)

---

## State Transitions (Authoritative)

**Valid state transitions:**
```
New → Active          (when starting work)
Active → Resolved     (work complete, pending review)
Resolved → Closed     (reviewed and approved)
Active → Closed       (work cancelled or rejected)
Any → Removed         (if cancelled)
```

**Always validate** before changing state. Use the most appropriate state for current work status.

---

## Norwegian Templates

**User Story (Brukerhistorie):**
```
Title: "Implementer [funksjon]"
Description: "Implementert [funksjon] med [detaljer]."
```

**Task (Oppgave):**
```
Title: "Opprett [komponent/funksjon]"
Description: "Opprettet [komponent] som [formål]."
```

**Bug (Feil):**
```
Title: "Fikset [problem]"
Description: "Fikset feil hvor [problembeskrivelse]. Løsning: [løsningsdetaljer]."
```

**Feature (Funksjonalitet):**
```
Title: "Ny funksjon: [funksjonsnavn]"
Description: "Implementert ny funksjon for å [formål]."
```

**Automatic Title Generation:**
- New function: `"Implementer funksjonen [FunctionName]"`
- Bug fix: `"Fikset feil: [ProblemDescription]"`
- Refactoring: `"Refaktorert [ComponentName]"`
- New script: `"Opprettet skript: [ScriptName]"`
- Configuration update: `"Oppdatert konfigurasjon for [System]"`

---

## Usage Examples

**Get work item details:**
```powershell
.\Azure-DevOpsUserStoryManager.ps1 -WorkItemId 12345 -Action Get
```

**Update description:**
```powershell
.\Azure-DevOpsUserStoryManager.ps1 -WorkItemId 12345 -Action Update `
    -Description "Updated requirements based on stakeholder feedback"
```

**Add comment:**
```powershell
.\Azure-DevOpsUserStoryManager.ps1 -WorkItemId 12345 -Action Comment `
    -Comment "Implementation completed and tested"
```

**Link code file:**
```powershell
.\Azure-DevOpsUserStoryManager.ps1 -WorkItemId 12345 -Action Link `
    -Url "DevTools/AdminTools/NewFeature/Implementation.ps1" `
    -Title "Implementation: Implementation.ps1"
```

**Change status:**
```powershell
.\Azure-DevOpsUserStoryManager.ps1 -WorkItemId 12345 -Action Status -State "Resolved"
```

**Add tags:**
```powershell
.\Azure-DevOpsUserStoryManager.ps1 -WorkItemId 12345 -Action AddTags `
    -Tags "Implemented;Tested;ReadyForReview"
```

---

## Context Detection

**Auto-detect work item ID from:**
- Branch names: `feature/12345-feature-name` → ID: 12345
- Commit messages: `"Fix #12345: Bug description"` → ID: 12345
- File comments: `# Related to work item 12345`
- User mentions: "This fixes story 12345"

**Auto-detect actions based on:**
- File changes: Link modified files to work item
- New documentation: Attach PDF/MD files
- Test files created: Create testing subtask
- README updates: Add documentation comment

---

## Best Practices

1. **Always link code files** when updating work items related to code changes
2. **Update status promptly** - Keep work item status current (Active during work, Resolved when done)
3. **Add context in comments** - Explain what was done and why, not just "done"
4. **Attach documentation** - Any specifications, designs, or documentation should be attached
5. **Create subtasks** - Break down large stories into manageable subtasks
6. **Tag appropriately** - Use tags for easy filtering and reporting

---

## Error Handling

If any command fails:
1. Report the error clearly with context
2. Suggest manual intervention if needed
3. Continue with remaining operations if applicable
4. Provide the work item URL for manual updates:
   `https://dev.azure.com/Dedge/Dedge/_workitems/edit/{WorkItemId}`

---

## Configuration

Uses GlobalFunctions configuration:
- `Get-AzureDevOpsOrganization` → "Dedge"
- `Get-AzureDevOpsProject` → "Dedge"
- `Get-AzureDevOpsPat` → PAT token (user-specific)
- `Get-AzureDevOpsRepository` → "DedgePsh"

**PAT Manager Location:** `DevTools/AzureTools/Azure-DevOpsPAT-Manager/`
